detaileddescription.para: An object representing a bi-directional RTP session. It holds sockets, jitter buffer, various counters (timestamp, sequence numbers...) Applications SHOULD NOT try to read things within the RtpSession object but use instead its public API (the rtp_session_* methods) where RtpSession is used as a pointer. rtp_session_new() allocates and initialize a RtpSession.
